.\" Manpage for simple_shell .hsh
.\" Contact 4718@holbertonschool.com or tluciad@gmail.com to correct errors.
.TH shell 1 "April 19, 2022" "Holberton School 0x16 - C" "shell man page"
.SH NAME
simple_shell to emulate the basics sh shell.
.B hsh \- a custom command language interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh [command_file] [argument...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The hsh utilitiy is a command language interpreter that executes commands read from a command 
line string, the standard input, or a specified file.
.SH INVOCATION
Compile simple_shell with the GNU Compiler Collection, preferably using gcc plus the below 
specified flags, as per this example (note the use of the * wildcard which enables all related .c files to be compiled concurrently):
.B $ gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic *.c -o hsh
Interactive mode
.B $ ./hsh
Non interactive mode
.B echo 'pwd' | ./hsh
.SH BUILTINS
The following builtin commands are supported:
.B 2. exit - exits shell.
.B 3. cd - changes directory.
.B 4. env - sifts environment
.BR PWD
This variable represents an absolute pathname of the current working directory.
.SH EXTENDED DESCRIPTION

.SH EXIT STATUS


.SH AUTHOR
Daniel Lopez, and Tania Diaz. See AUTHORS file for more detail.
